			   SWIG for elastiC
			   ================

INTRODUCTION
------------

elastiC is a portable high-level object-oriented interpreted language
with a C like syntax.
SWIG (Simplified Wrapper and Interface Generator) is a tool generating
the necessary "glue" C code to use a C/C++ library from interpreted
languages. This module is an attempt to extend SWIG giving it support
for the elastiC language.
SWIG can be found at:

  http://www.swig.org
  ftp://ftp.swig.org

(get version 1.1p5)

USAGE
-----

To use SWIG for elastiC read SWIG documentation before, than read the
examples in this package.
To start using it you'll need to compile and install it before (see the
INSTALLATION section below).

ELASTIC WEB SITE
----------------

elastiC official web site is:

    http://www.elasticworld.org

You'll find here the most recent release, documentation, support
and other valuable information, in addition to many modules.

INSTALLATION
------------

SWIG for elastiC makes use of automake & autoconf.
To compile it, simply issue the commands:

  % configure
  % make
  % make install

You can specify to configure where you have installed SWIG; for
example, if you have SWIG in /usr:

  % configure --with-swig=/usr

(please note that SWIG for elastiC has been tested only on SWIG
version 1.1p5).
For a full list of options, do a 'configure --help'.
There is also an example directory (named 'examples' :). You can
compile the examples by making:

  % make examples

For a more complete explanation of the compilation process, see
the file "INSTALL".

